cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper presents a framework for hyperspectral image change detection using a 2-D convolutional neural network. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also involves the use of subpixel representation and the exploration of abundance information, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper uses a mixed-affinity matrix to fuse multisource information, which may indicate a connection to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category.
